<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,402,1153]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1499315587" country="Brazil" location="Solimoes River" municipality="Penera River" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,984,1009]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
Eurides Furtado (private collection, Appendix) provided photographs of two females seemingly of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,301,1020,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rebeli" subSpecies="cuprea">
<emphasis box="[151,301,1020,1044]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">rebeli cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[372,443,1020,1045]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[457,578,1021,1045]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, Maués (
<collectingMunicipality box="[681,835,1020,1045]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Penera River</collectingMunicipality>
). Note that the examined material includes one male and two females from the Amazonian municipality of Manacapuru, which extends north and south of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BB87F4FFBFFF9AE1FF235FBB91FB7D:8ECD6039FFBFFF9AE45C2658BAA5FBA1" country="Brazil" municipality="Penera River" name="Solimoes River" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" stateProvince="Amazonas">Solimões River</location>
. Although we find it less likely that 
<taxonomicName box="[646,832,1092,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rebeli" subSpecies="cuprea">
<emphasis box="[646,832,1092,1116]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">B. rebeli cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected north of the Solimões, this should be confirmed in future fieldwork.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
